#X text 265 188 Trackster allows defining sections in a track (presets: Drum & Bass) to control events in a formally structured way. The abstraction uses input bangs and calculates bars \, section and total track length based on the note resolution given. The default is 8ths \, input bangs e.g. via a metro object in a given tempo in 8ths \, each bar then has a 4/4 (8/8) meter., f 57;
#X text 17 435, f 71;
#X text 17 385 Outlets for each track section defined above. Outputs 1s on each bang received via inlet when section is currently active \, 0s when section is not active. Use these to activate elements in respective track sections or trigger events defined outside this abstraction., f 71;
#X text 17 455 Info: most send/receive objects are not using locality prefixes. Until this is changed \, don't use more than one trackster.pd abstraction in your patch!, f 55;
